# piggabap — a cartoon barnyard chase for synthesized marimba.
#
# Style: comic mock-menace, Carl-Stalling-flavored. Playful pigs in
# mud, frantic curious snorting, fast and grinning — never genuinely
# chaotic. Each phrase below has an unspoken syllabic chant the
# xylophone squeals as if a pig had learned to sing. The voices are
# layered, not arranged as a single line.
#
# This is marimbaba's farmyard cousin. F minor lends the comic-mock-
# menace cartoon-flavor: tight, fast, grinning. A 40-second pop romp.
#
# Key: F natural minor (F G Ab Bb C Db Eb). 4/4, ~144 BPM
# (1 beat ≈ 0.417 s, 1 bar ≈ 1.667 s).
# Form: 24 bars / ~40 s. The score lives at piggabap.np; the actual
# event scheduling + mix lives in bin/render-piggabap.mjs.
#
# Voices:
#   xylophone      — the pig's high voice (squeals — the lead)
#   bass           — low F/C oinks (the deep grunt)
#   staccato       — sharp dry snorts (percussive marimba slap)
#   woodblock      — clip-clop trotters (the chase)
#
# Harmony: i (Fm) – iv (Bbm) – v (Cm) – VI (Db) – i (Fm).
# Bass on F2 + C3 alternating, very tight pulse.
#
# ── unspoken lyric, syllable-by-syllable ──────────────────────────────
#
# [oink] — bars 1–4 — descending F minor third triads
#   bar 1:  oink         OINK                          (F5 ─ Db5)
#   bar 2:  oink         OINK                          (Db5 ─ Bb4)
#   bar 3:  oink-oink    OINK                          (F5 Db5 Bb4)
#   bar 4:  OINK                                       (F5 held)
#
# [snort] — bars 5–10 — fast 16th-note bursts
#   bar 5:  snort-snort  SNORT                         (F5 Ab5 C6)
#   bar 6:  snort-snort  SNORT-snort                   (F5 Ab5 C6 Eb6)
#   bar 7:  snort        SNORT                         (Eb6 C6)
#   bar 8:  snort-snort  SNORT                         (Ab5 C6 Eb6)
#   bar 9:  snort-snort  snort-SNORT                   (F5 Ab5 C6 Eb6)
#   bar 10: SNORT                                      (Eb6 held)
#
# [mud] — bars 11–14 — rolling chromatic squelches
#   bar 11: mud-MUD-mud                                (F5 E5 Eb5 F5)
#   bar 12: roll-A-ROUND                               (F5 Db5 F5 Ab5)
#   bar 13: mud-MUD-mud                                (Bb5 Ab5 G5 F5)
#   bar 14: SQUELCH                                    (F5 held, woodblock clops)
#
# [chase] — bars 15–20 — climb-descend zigzag, all voices in
#   bar 15: chase-the    CAT                           (F5 C6 Ab5 Eb6)
#   bar 16: chase-the    CAT                           (Eb6 Ab5 C6 F5)
#   bar 17: round-the    BARN                          (F5 Ab5 C6 Eb6)
#   bar 18: round-the    BARN                          (Eb6 C6 Ab5 F5)
#   bar 19: catch-her    CATCH-her                     (F5 C6 F5 Eb6)
#   bar 20: GOTCHA                                     (C6 Ab5 F5 Db5)
#
# [flop] — bars 21–24 — settle and snore
#   bar 21: flop         FLOP                          (Db5 ─ Bb4)
#   bar 22: flop                                       (Ab4 held)
#   bar 23: SNORE                                      (F4 held)
#   bar 24: (sleep)                                    (F4 held, long)
#
# Below: section markers for the renderer (sections by name).

# oink 4 [bass, xylophone]
F5:_*2 Db5:_*2
Db5:_*2 Bb4:_*2
F5:_*1 Db5:_*1 Bb4:_*2
F5:_*4

